cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.CL

This paper deals with the analysis of mobile sensing data and the development of machine learning-based personality models. The paper focuses on the cultural impact of users' country of residence on model replicability. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society) as the paper deals with the impact of culture on technology. The paper also involves machine learning-based personality models, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the most predictive data categories, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper discusses the possibility of technology personalization, which falls under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
